Although sometimes
you run into a straggler

15:17.584 --> 15:20.451
who ended up neither
here nor there.

15:22.221 --> 15:26.190
And one time, I saw a bag
of bones wearing a bikini.

15:26.192 --> 15:27.258
I'm so sorry.

15:27.260 --> 15:28.726
That must have been awful.

15:28.728 --> 15:30.428
Well, I ain't gonna lie to you.

15:30.430 --> 15:34.065
The sight of a bikini
still does it for me.

15:34.067 --> 15:35.566
Skin or no.

15:35.568 --> 15:39.604
Yeah, I'm more of a
skin guy, myself.

15:39.606 --> 15:42.340
Different strokes.

15:45.210 --> 15:47.412
So...

15:47.414 --> 15:49.981
still think your family's alive?

15:55.120 --> 15:57.188
Let's get the hell
out of here.

15:58.891 --> 16:01.592
Oh, uh, uh
now I got you here.

16:01.594 --> 16:04.495
There is one thing
I've been really itching to do.

16:14.840 --> 16:18.142
(yells)
Forty-love!

16:18.144 --> 16:20.011
Get in the game.

16:21.647 --> 16:23.181
Ace!

16:24.149 --> 16:25.817
Ace!

16:25.819 --> 16:27.285
I wasn't even set.

16:27.287 --> 16:28.319
What do you mean?
You got to be

16:28.321 --> 16:29.487
on your toes, man.

16:29.489 --> 16:30.855
You got to be
on your toes.

16:30.857 --> 16:32.523
That's game.

16:32.525 --> 16:34.292
You owe me
a Lamborghini.

16:34.294 --> 16:35.760
(whoops, laughing)

16:35.762 --> 16:37.028
(ice cream truck music plays)

16:37.030 --> 16:39.597
You a cookie guy?

16:39.599 --> 16:42.700
I got some great cookies
back in the boat.

16:42.702 --> 16:45.770
I mean they're, you know,
they're three years old,

16:45.772 --> 16:47.005
but they're still good.

16:47.007 --> 16:48.172
Uh, y... you know,
I used to date

16:48.174 --> 16:50.975
this Italian girl,
Antonella.

16:50.977 --> 16:53.044
She turned me on to them--
biscottis.

16:53.046 --> 16:55.980
You know, they're stale,
but on purpose.

16:55.982 --> 16:57.015
Hard as a brick.

16:57.017 --> 16:59.484
So was her backside.

16:59.486 --> 17:01.319
I di... well... oh.

17:01.321 --> 17:02.987
(tires squeal)
Okay, hold on here.

17:02.989 --> 17:05.189
What are you doing?
Got to do a
little detour here.

17:05.191 --> 17:07.458
Just got to go back.
I can see the boat from here.

17:07.460 --> 17:08.559
Just-just trust me.

17:08.561 --> 17:10.161
This is a much
better way, man.

17:10.163 --> 17:12.163
Whoa, whoa, hey,
whoa, whoa, what is that?
What?

17:12.165 --> 17:14.832
Th-that billboard up there.
What billboard?

17:14.834 --> 17:17.035
What are you doing?
Will you slow down?
All right, no problem.

17:17.703 --> 17:20.571
Stop the...
Hey! (grunts)

17:20.573 --> 17:22.306
(tires squeal)

17:22.308 --> 17:24.509
Gah...

17:24.511 --> 17:26.544
There's nothing to see!

17:26.546 --> 17:28.813
Oh, oh, my God.

17:28.815 --> 17:30.148
Hey!

17:30.150 --> 17:31.716
Look at that, you see that?
Look!

17:31.718 --> 17:33.651
Alive in Tucson.

17:33.653 --> 17:34.652
That's where I'm from.

17:34.654 --> 17:36.421
That's... I'm from Tucson.

17:36.423 --> 17:37.822
Well, I mean
that's where my family...

17:37.824 --> 17:39.590
(grunts)

17:39.592 --> 17:42.560
You should have stayed
in the truck, bud.

17:48.834 --> 17:51.702
YOUNG TANDY:
Oh, my God, not again.

17:51.704 --> 17:53.871
You are so stupid.

17:53.873 --> 17:56.040
There's only, like,
one other dude,

17:56.042 --> 17:58.676
and you let him
hit you with a wrench.

17:58.678 --> 18:02.447
You beefed it so hard.
You beefed it.

18:02.449 --> 18:05.083
I'm not the one lying
in the middle of the street.

18:05.085 --> 18:07.585
Now get up, fartface.

18:07.587 --> 18:10.021
Come on, you flippin' turd.

18:10.023 --> 18:11.055
I can't get up, Phil.

18:11.057 --> 18:12.390
I can't move.

18:12.392 --> 18:14.058
Well, if you're just
going to quit,

18:14.060 --> 18:16.694
then I'm going
to pee on you.
What?

18:16.696 --> 18:18.062
'Cause that's what
happens to quitters.

18:18.064 --> 18:19.797
They get peed on.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.766
Well, go for it. See if I care.

18:21.768 --> 18:24.102
I'm wearing a friggin'
hazmat suit, you dong.

18:24.104 --> 18:25.770
Fine. Here I go.

18:25.772 --> 18:27.138
No, please, don't,
don't, don't, don't.

18:27.140 --> 18:28.906
Don't look at my ween,
you pervert.

18:28.908 --> 18:30.875
I'm not looking
at your ween.
Three.

18:30.877 --> 18:32.410
Please, just don't do it,
Phil, okay?

18:32.412 --> 18:34.946
Two.
(crying):
Please, don't. Stop.

18:34.948 --> 18:36.714
One.

18:36.716 --> 18:38.216
(Young Tandy laughing)

18:38.218 --> 18:40.318
PAT:
♪ Washing clean,
bleaching clean ♪

18:40.320 --> 18:43.221
♪ Virus go away, virus... ♪

18:44.456 --> 18:45.890
Hi, Mike.

18:45.892 --> 18:47.225
What did you do?

18:47.227 --> 18:49.227
I hit you in the head
with a wrench.

18:49.229 --> 18:50.261
You're welcome, by the way.

18:50.263 --> 18:51.496
I saved your your life.

18:51.498 --> 18:52.830
You know, you don't want
to go to Tucson.

18:52.832 --> 18:54.398
And if you think about it,

18:54.400 --> 18:56.501
who would want to go there?

18:56.503 --> 18:58.302
Well, I'll tell you who...
the government.

18:58.304 --> 18:59.804
It's a big booby trap.

18:59.806 --> 19:02.507
The whole city's
a giant crematorium.

19:02.509 --> 19:04.642
They're just waiting
for the signal to rebuild.

19:04.644 --> 19:06.077
So that all those people
who are living

19:06.079 --> 19:07.778
in the government bunkers
can come out.

19:07.780 --> 19:09.580
Yeah? Well, you're going
to have to shoot me,

19:09.582 --> 19:10.781
'cause I'm going.

19:10.783 --> 19:12.984
Okay, all... then I will.

19:12.986 --> 19:16.287
I-I've really enjoyed
our time together,

19:16.289 --> 19:17.421
but I will shoot you.

19:17.423 --> 19:18.589
Fine.

19:18.591 --> 19:19.790
Just lay back down, look,

19:19.792 --> 19:21.159
hey, I got to get your backside,

19:21.161 --> 19:23.427
so just turn over.

19:23.429 --> 19:25.429
Oh, you laid in something.

19:25.431 --> 19:27.598
It's like virus.

19:31.503 --> 19:33.838
(grunting)
Hey.

19:35.207 --> 19:37.275
(groaning)

19:38.544 --> 19:40.344
(grunting)

19:41.780 --> 19:43.481
(thud)

19:43.483 --> 19:46.784
Sorry, buddy.

19:51.290 --> 19:52.690
Is that a rip?

19:56.695 --> 19:59.530
Damn it!

19:59.532 --> 20:02.533
(frustrated crying)

20:02.535 --> 20:05.236
(crying)

20:07.906 --> 20:10.908
Sorry, bud.

20:10.910 --> 20:12.877
You had a good run.

20:16.048 --> 20:18.115
(rustling)

20:24.223 --> 20:26.390
(zipper opening)

20:36.868 --> 20:39.403
R-I-P Spaceman.

20:39.405 --> 20:42.240
Cause of death:
the "goverment."

20:43.208 --> 20:45.743
Almost got it right.

20:47.946 --> 20:50.014
(laughs softly)

20:52.217 --> 20:54.285
♪ ♪

20:55.354 --> 20:57.421
(siren wailing)

20:58.790 --> 21:01.959
♪ When I get off
of this mountain ♪

21:01.961 --> 21:03.961
♪ You know where I want to go ♪

21:05.530 --> 21:08.532
♪ Straight down
the Mississippi River ♪

21:08.534 --> 21:10.768
♪ To the Gulf of Mexico ♪

21:11.770 --> 21:14.705
♪ To Lake Charles, Louisiana ♪

21:14.707 --> 21:17.308
♪ Little Bessie,
girl that I once knew... ♪

21:18.910 --> 21:22.280
Do you like tennis?

21:22.282 --> 21:26.884
♪ Up on Cripple Creek,
she sends me ♪

21:26.886 --> 21:30.288
♪ If I spring a leak,
she mends me ♪

21:30.290 --> 21:32.056
♪ I don't have to speak ♪

21:32.058 --> 21:33.491
♪ 'Cause she defends me ♪

21:33.493 --> 21:38.129
♪ A drunkard's dream
if I ever did see one ♪

21:40.565 --> 21:42.767
♪ Good luck had just stung me ♪

21:42.769 --> 21:47.571
